{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Getting Started - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Getting Started with Wisp</h1>

<p>Wisp is a secure, high-performance HTML templating engine for Go with a Liquid-inspired syntax.</p>

<h2>Why Wisp?</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Security-first: HTML auto-escaping enabled by default</li>
  <li>Familiar syntax: Liquid-inspired, easy to read and write</li>
  <li>Performance: Template caching and scope pooling</li>
  <li>Composable: Include, render, and component systems</li>
</ul>

<h2>Installation</h2>
<pre><code>go get template-wisp</code></pre>

<h2>Quick Start</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}package main

import (
    "fmt"
    "template-wisp/pkg/engine"
)

func main() {
    e := engine.New()
    template := "Hello, {%.name%}!"
    data := map[string]interface{}{"name": "World"}
    result, _ := e.RenderString(template, data)
    fmt.Println(result)
}{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Basic Syntax</h2>
<h3>Variables</h3>
<p>Access with dot: <code>{% raw %}{%.name%}{% endraw %}</code></p>

<h3>Filters</h3>
<p>Transform: <code>{% raw %}{%.name | upcase %}{% endraw %}</code></p>

<h3>Conditionals</h3>
<p><code>{% raw %}{% if .show %}...{% end %}{% endraw %}</code></p>

<h3>Loops</h3>
<p><code>{% raw %}{% for .item in .items %}...{% end %}{% endraw %}</code></p>

<h2>Template Composition</h2>
<p>Three ways: include, render, component</p>

<h2>Layout System</h2>
<p>Use extends and block tags</p>

